The paper focuses on understanding user behavior and motivations on Wikipedia, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and social media (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper uses a large-scale survey to gather data, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
